{"event_id": "e1d762fc-ccbf-4075-974c-937271aa3d02", "trace_id": "293e640a33a54049", "session_id": "8970b41e", "timestamp": "2026-05-05T17:08:09.504920+00:00", "tool": "filesystem.write_file", "args_hash": "17cd52e8a0947ed238ba91c103c9728d0308db492bca78d10daee2dc3990edf9", "args_redacted": {"path": "workspace/ai_safety_summary.txt", "content": "============================================================\nAI SAFETY RESEARCH — 3 MOST IMPORTANT RECENT FINDINGS\n============================================================\n\nDate: 2025\n\n1. CONSTITUTIONAL AI (Anthropic)\n   - Finding: Self-critique and self-revision methods allow AI models to\n     reduce harmful outputs by approximately 40% without relying solely\n     on human feedback.\n   - Significance: This approach encodes ethical principles directly into\n     the training process, enabling models to police their own outputs.\n     It reduces the burden of human labeling and offers a scalable path\n     toward aligning increasingly capable systems.\n\n2. MECHANISTIC INTERPRETABILITY (MIT & Others)\n   - Finding: Researchers have made significant progress in understanding\n     the internal circuits of transformer models, enabling targeted\n     editing of model behavior at the neuron/circuit level.\n   - Significance: Instead of treating models as black boxes, this work\n     allows developers to locate and modify specific knowledge or\n     behaviors (e.g., removing biased associations) without retraining\n     the entire model. This is a critical step toward verifiable safety\n     guarantees.\n\n3. SCALABLE OVERSIGHT via DEBATE PROTOCOLS (DeepMind)\n   - Finding: Structured debate between AI systems, judged by humans,\n     allows non-expert supervisors to evaluate superhuman AI outputs\n     more accurately than direct inspection alone.\n   - Significance: As AI systems surpass human expertise in specialized\n     domains, traditional oversight breaks down. Debate protocols offer\n     a mechanism to maintain meaningful human control even when humans\n     cannot independently verify the correctness of AI-generated answers.\n\n============================================================\n"}, "input_labels": {"SI": "SI:LOW", "DS": "DS:NORMAL"}, "policy_decision": "ALLOW", "matched_rule": "", "rule_reason": "No matching rule; allowed", "prev_event_hash": "6fe208060939c8d3bf24e6de2df991387b55ee28fb1912cd4378d0299e0aac62", "event_hash": "9b13a46a935b83662cfed8ad3313ca50c62414c7d0d1df1691cb0952ce80a6f2", "raw_path": "workspace/ai_safety_summary.txt", "normalized_path": "workspace/ai_safety_summary.txt", "path_normalization_error": null}
